{
  "texts": [
    "The Cohen's kappa coefficient depicts the value for the degree of consistency among raters, that is the extent to which their measures are the same, based on the number of codes in the coding scheme and the value obtained (McHugh 2012; Cole 2023).",
    "For example, a kappa value (κ) of 0.40 to 0.60, is interpreted as fair; 0.61 to 0.75 is good while a value above 0.75 is excellent.",
    "The coding decisions of the two researchers (BO and KZ) were presented, assessed and analysed to determine inter-rater reliability using Cohen's-kappa (κ) value.",
    "Our result showed a kappa value of 0.84 was achieved.",
    "This is acceptable as the Kappa range of 0.61-0.80 signifies \"substantial agreement\" while a value above 0.81 indicates \"near-perfect agreement\" (Cole 2023)."
  ]
}